    "finalTextLength": 1255,
    "finalText": "Teams messages from this past week don’t reveal any actionable signals about major worries. My search across all vectorized Teams messages returned zero matching records specific to current concerns, risks, or stresses—at least within the evidence that’s been successfully synced and embedded. Given the current degraded sync status (including a critical backlog for Teams DM exports on acannon@alleatogroup.com), it’s possible relevant chats haven’t been ingested yet.\n\nHere’s what that means:\n- No clear escalation, flags, or problem threads appear in the Teams evidence I can access for the last seven days.\n- Evidence is thin due to the embedding backlog—don’t treat this as confirmation that nobody has concerns; treat it as a gap in current visibility, especially for high-velocity or DM conversations.\n\n**What to do next:**  \nIf you want a real-time pulse, consider supplementing this with a quick email or call-out in your existing team cadence. If there are specific people or channels you suspect are worried but haven’t surfaced it in meetings, name them and I can dig specifically.\n\nSummary: No concrete worries logged in Teams this week—but tool coverage is incomplete. If you need targeted follow-up, tell me who or what project to pinpoint.",
